🧠 DOM Manipulation with JavaScript — Reference Card
🌐 What Is the DOM?
The Document Object Model (DOM) is a programming interface for HTML/XML documents.

It represents the page as a hierarchical tree of nodes, allowing programs to modify structure, style, and content.

Created by W3C, it's language-agnostic but most commonly used with JavaScript.

🧩 DOM Structure
Root node: <html>

Child nodes: <head>, <body>

Nested nodes: <title>, <h1>, <p>, etc.

🛠️ Accessing Elements
Method	Description	Example
getElementById()	Selects one element by ID	document.getElementById("header")
getElementsByClassName()	Selects all elements with a class	document.getElementsByClassName("info")
querySelector()	Selects the first match	document.querySelector(".info")
querySelectorAll()	Selects all matches	document.querySelectorAll(".info")
✏️ Modifying Elements
Text: element.textContent = "New text"

HTML: element.innerHTML = "<strong>Bold</strong>"

Attributes: element.setAttribute("src", "newLogo.png")

Styles: element.style.color = "blue"

let newParagraph = document.createElement("p");
newParagraph.textContent = "This is a new paragraph.";
document.body.appendChild(newParagraph);

let oldElement = document.getElementById("oldElement");
oldElement.parentNode.removeChild(oldElement);

let newElement = document.createElement("p");
newElement.textContent = "New Data";
document.body.appendChild(newElement);

